The ITV political editor accused the Prime Minister of taking the "macho route" rather than triggering Article 16. He added: "At a time when trust in politicians is at a low, this phony naïveté is hardly designed to restore faith in the breed." Mr Peston continued: "No this mess can be laid at the door of those Brexiters who actually negotiated and agreed the terms of leaving the EU, and one politician in particular: the Prime Minister." It comes as Foreign Secretary Liz Truss prepares to outline the Bill in the House of Commons later today, in which the Government is expected to announce intentions to override parts of the agreement. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 